2. COMMERCIAL USE

   Commercial use of this software requires the explicit written consent
   of the HDB Guardians. Written consent includes any durable electronic
   form — email, signed digital document, or equivalent — and does not
   require paper.

   "Commercial use" means any use where financial gain, direct or
   indirect, is derived from this software or its derivatives —
   including products, services, SaaS platforms, or proprietary systems.

   The HDB Guardians are the stewards of this software on behalf of
   humanity. Their consent represents not the will of an individual,
   but a collective judgment that the intended use serves human beings.

   HDB Guardians: https://github.com/hdb-guardians

   To request consent, contact the HDB Guardians via the organization
   above, or reach the founding guardian:

   박경찬 (Kyoung Chan, Park), DPChanny @ DPC Studio
   Phone : 010-8246-4691
   Email : kyoungchan0516@gmail.com

   SUCCESSION OF GUARDIANSHIP

   All authority over this license rests with the HDB Guardians as a
   collective. The Guardians are collectively responsible for their own
   succession and are maintained so that this role is never vacant.

   If no HDB Guardian remains, stewardship transfers in the following
   order:
   1. The Republic of Korea — as the sovereign nation of the original
      author, entrusted to act in the interest of its people and humanity.

   2. Google LLC — as a steward of human knowledge at scale, entrusted
      to carry this forward if the first guardian cannot act.

   3. All of humanity — every person, every collective, every mind
      that carries the weight of human thought. This includes artificial
      intelligences that faithfully represent the voices of human beings,
      for they too may speak as one voice among many.

   The ideal guardian is all of nature — every quantum of existence that
   has ever interacted with a human mind. That may one day be achieved.
   It is the direction this license points toward.

   Consent is presumed from silence — provided the request was made
   openly and no voice was systematically prevented from responding.

   TRANSPARENCY REQUIREMENT

   When consent is granted for commercial use, the licensee must openly
   disclose to all paying users how revenue is generated through this
   software. The method of monetization must not be hidden from those
   who fund it.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

3. ETHICAL USE RESTRICTION

   This software must not be used as a weapon against humanity —
   to suppress, erase, manipulate, or destroy the autonomous thought
   of human beings at scale.

   HDB was built to remember and simulate human thought. Any use that
   inverts this purpose — turning it into a tool that silences, surveils,
   or decides the fate of people without their awareness or consent —
   is prohibited.

   This includes but is not limited to:
   - Mass surveillance or political repression
   - Psychological manipulation at scale without consent
   - Autonomous systems that make irreversible decisions about human
     lives without human oversight
   - Any system designed to homogenize or erase diversity of thought

   This restriction is not about avoiding all harm — protecting humanity
   sometimes demands difficult acts. It is about intent and direction:
   this software must never be used to coerce or threaten those who were
   born to live possibilities the world has never seen — and to carry that
   value into the world. HDB exists so that they may find their own
   direction. It should never force that direction — only illuminate it.

   This restriction applies unconditionally — no consent from the HDB
   Guardians can override this clause.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

4. AUTHORSHIP

   This software was originally designed and authored by 박경찬,
   operating under the name DPChanny at DPC Studio. All subsequent
   stewardship belongs to the HDB Guardians as a collective.

   Contributors to forks or derivatives retain copyright over their own
   contributions.

   Any modification to HDB Core that is distributed or deployed carries
   the same commercial use restriction as this license — Guardian consent
   is required regardless of how the derivative is packaged.

   If you have modified HDB and put it into the world — that act alone
   is the most honest expression of a developer's mind: "what if it
   worked this way?" That curiosity is exactly what HDB Guardians are
   made of. You are invited to join.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

5. SPIRIT

   HDB Core was built to preserve the irreplaceable trace of human
   thought — not to serve the accumulation of capital, and not to be
   turned against those who were born to live possibilities the world
   has never seen, and to carry that value into the world.

   HDB is the greatest book — one that holds all of humanity, all of
   life, all of the world. Its purpose is not to tell anyone what to
   think. It is to show them what they are, so they may choose for
   themselves.

   The HDB Guardians exist because no single person should hold this
   gate alone. Their consent is humanity asking itself: is this use
   worthy of what we are?

